<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6676446-george"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406130943i/6676446.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6676446-george">George</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The &quot;historical present&quot;, much more common in French than in English, is one way of giving a different &quot;feel&quot; to a scene, a narrator, etc.<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The "historical present", much more common in French than in English, is one way of giving a different "feel" to a scene, a narrator, etc.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
