<span id="freeTextContainer453579429122346290">Second read: August 2020 <br/>Medium: Audio<br/>Rating: ⭐⭐⭐⭐ <br/><br/>*****<br/><b>3.85-this-book-is-epic-believe-all-the-hype-stars</b><br/><b>
  <i>Tigana</i>
</b> is a book that will put you through all the emotions that exist. I am seriously exhausted (in a good way). Reading this book was a great experience. Some of the best characters that I have read in a long time. The story build-up is awesome, to epic proportions. By the time the book reached its climax I was all clammy-palmed-stuttering-heart-hanging-from-the-edge-of-my-seat <s>no,finge</s></span>
  <span id="freeText453579429122346290" style="display:none">Second read: August 2020 <br />Medium: Audio<br />Rating: ⭐⭐⭐⭐ <br /><br />*****<br /><b>3.85-this-book-is-epic-believe-all-the-hype-stars</b><br /><b>
  <i>Tigana</i>
</b> is a book that will put you through all the emotions that exist. I am seriously exhausted (in a good way). Reading this book was a great experience. Some of the best characters that I have read in a long time. The story build-up is awesome, to epic proportions. By the time the book reached its climax I was all clammy-palmed-stuttering-heart-hanging-from-the-edge-of-my-seat <s>no,fingernails not bitten to stubbs at all</s>. <br />BUT<br /><br />Something fell a notch short for me in the last quarter of the book. I just probably had started to expect too much, so feeling wayyyyy more let down, than I should. And one of those rare times when I was actually not interested in any of the romantic entaglements well except for <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ Dianora and Brandin. One pair I was badly rooting for. The other one felt too contrived and the third, not even necessary. Strange how I was actually hoping that the bad guy would be spared so that he can have his happy ending :(  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br />Still an amazing read, definitely putting it to my re-reads shelf!</span>
